at Corkers' Institute, where we hope to hear Maj Gen Howard, and H. W. Beecher. Bothe of whom we heard yesterday morning at the Am Messy Assn on the subject of the Freedman, their condition and wants. Tomorrow will be the Jubilee Bible Meeting. The meetings which we have had so far (4 in Number) were excellent meetings - the one this morning was the Am.Finch Society - a very excellent meeting indeed. Your mother is taking a little rest this afternoon, while I am writing this. We both feel pretty well, - we do not expect to visit but little - attending meetings is about all we can do this week. We were glad that Anna was not feeling any worse after the visit to Hugh James's - and that you had that pleasant visit by R. Hughes and Jane - and Lewis and Jane in the evening. Probably you will not get our first letter till this evening, and this one tomorrow evening - Our kind respects to all our neighbors that you may see and much love our loved ones at home.
From your 
Pa and Ma

Remsen Pine 10/5. My Dear Daughter. I received your letter last evening and was very glad hear from you, Had a letter from unclear by the same man? and they were well but felt gave? an account of the state of things there your father borrowed who sent him 200 dollars to pay for his claim John says the baby will get up and stand in the middle of the, and he can walk by the chairs We had a letter from Mary this evening she says her health is better but that she does not feel very well, Dr says she had better stay there few weeks, and she does not know how long she will stay and that we must not expect her home still

we see her, I hope Elizabeth and you will try not to be uneasy about her, if she does intervene she had better there a little longer Jane and I had just written to her and sent off before we got her Jane and Sarah have been making Eddie a vest and hat? and unclear and I another harp?, Jane and Sarah have unclear there? and sew? is Jane and children gone to her NY? this evening it is very wet weather here it is guide wet? to night last my? thundered and lightened and rained for 3 or 4 hours had a letter from your father this eve from unclear he was to start, from there () yesterday morning to go to the 6 o'clock had meetings there today and start tomorrow morning 3 o AM and be in Chicago to preach tomorrow eve and on to Racine against the Sabbath, he will call unclear uncle in coming back? from this I will write to you again when I hear from Mary, Mother

My Dear Daughter It is as much as three long weeks since we heard from you what can be the reason we are very anxious, I thunk we wrote twice last week, and sent Elizabeth to letter to Cynthia, have not written to Elizabeth till we hear from you Mary says she thinks you are preparing for examination, but we fear you are sick if so let us know and let us know the whole, will not some one offer your letter and write us, I would not tax you with a long letter if you are crowded It is a long time since we heard from John we can not account for their silence, Mary's health is improving Sarah is rather feeble
Needs Review

your father is going to the village and I (will) send this please write soon if you have not written, what books do you want us to send do you wish to have them all, they will be very heavy if we send them all Much love from each at home your Mother Eliz Everett Jan 25 Cynthia is very anxious to hear from you as she does not know how to decide

Friday RM Dear Son and Daughter We are yet blocked in no path for butter to the store, Eddy is going a foot with letters to the village, Tommy took them there yesterday and forgot to leave these I opened Sarah and write this in, If does not snow today hope they will open the road, we have not had only one mail this week not your letter I unclear yesterday Lewis is in unclear since sunday if he comes as far as stone felen? I do not know now he might come home we never saw so much snow

the came on snow shoes John and Griffith called here yesterday fell us levers had some trouble Sunday to get to Janes home John I and Lewis were at the tolls, they only one printed ticket the other one was written, they were discouraged to come to have it printed, it was what they call the hill ticket that was printed this one carried we are all will and unite in love to you both, we do not know but the snow will prevent father young to unclear as I said anyway love? Mother

Clinton Mon eve May 10 My Dear Daughters Your very welcome better? to Sarah we received last Saturday she was then well enough to hear me read it and for me to be at some distance from the bed we were glad to fined that you spent the vacation relaxing? and I trust profitable and that your health was good the had a letter from father on friday but he did not say anything about Jane returning and I feel anxious to know she meant to be there this week I am very sorry for her to lose any of this term but it could not be helped o Mary I wish you knew how Sarah has gained there two days her teeth have stoped working but her face is swelled saturday night she was very restful and did not sleep much sunday she was easy in and slept () had a good night last night and to day she is very much better I hope I may go home soon, the Doctor and Mr Kellogg s family thought she would not
Needs Review

Mrs Butler was there she said can folks were will in Whiteshom Robert was going home that afternoon to spend the sabbath with Jane, I expect to have a letter from home today I must close we both gain? in have to you sarah say. she will not be able to answer your letter soon as she must be careful not to overdo for some time Your affectionate Mother Elizabeth Everett

Dear daughters Sarah and Cynthia- Your sisters got here to Ithica- and Anna reached home Saturday after noon well- after their good visit to Saratoga.- We all join in love to you- Your Father.
Needs Review

Monday Morn- Dear Daughters, Sarah + Cynthia- We were much gratified with a visit today from her + hers wood- they had hard time to come up through the deep mud from rest? being fast "Harm" to our house- It was great love to you that urged them to come. We said by unclear $10 for you to get home things for summer clothes- Jane will write (I think) today or tomorrow- Your mother was with me to Prospect to a meeting last evening- the roads were very bad indeed But it is faire Summer weather now- and the roads will be town? settled now - All well and join in love to you- thanking Cynthia for being so functional and constant in her correspondence Your unclear father + mother Robert and Elizabeth Everett
Needs Review

Dear Daughters
It is so long since I have written to you, that I must write some if it is only a little. We feel rejoiced to hear that you have good and interesting meetings- hope it will continue and increase, and that the members of your school may be blessed. -- We feel for you in the responsible situation you are placed in, we pray that you may be supported and directed. May you get good and be enabled to do good. I fear least your duties will tax your strength too much, can you not arrange so as to have more time to rest, remember health
